snippet: The Commerce Department said housing starts rose 6.9 percent in June to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 760,000 units, the highest since October 2008.
abstract: Commerce Department says housing starts rose 6.9 percent in June, to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 760,000, highest rate since October 2008; new permits for building homes fell 3.7 percent, to an annual 755,000 unit pace.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department said housing starts rose 6.9 percent in June to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 760,000 units, the highest since October 2008.

headline.seo: Housing Starts Are Up, but Building Permits Decline
